  <h1>How Plant‑Based Meals Influence&nbsp;Hormonal&nbsp;Balance&nbsp;and Mood</h1>

  <!--—‑‑  Hero image  —‑‑-->
  <img src="../assets/images/how-plant-based.png"
       alt="Assorted colorful plant‑based foods arranged on a table"
       class="hero-img" />

  <!--—‑‑  Intro / 導讀段落  —‑‑-->
  <section class="introduction">
    <p>Curious how your dinner plate might affect your inner balance? This article explores the science behind plant‑based meals and their powerful impact on your hormones and emotional well‑being.</p>
  </section>

  <!--—‑‑  Section 1  —‑‑-->
  <article class="section">
    <h2>🌿 Introduction: The Mood‑Food Connection</h2>
    <p>
      Modern nutritional science increasingly confirms what ancient healing systems have long believed:
      what we eat doesn’t just shape our body—it also shapes our emotions. Hormonal balance plays a crucial role in how
      we feel, sleep, focus, and manage stress. With plant‑based diets gaining popularity, it’s important to ask:
      can this dietary shift influence our hormonal health and emotional stability?
    </p>
  </article>

  <!--—‑‑  Section 2  —‑‑-->
  <article class="section">
    <h2>🌱 Key Hormones That Affect Mood</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Serotonin</strong>: Often called the “feel‑good hormone,” it helps regulate mood, sleep, and appetite.</li>
      <li><strong>Cortisol</strong>: Known as the “stress hormone,” it spikes during anxiety or physical strain.</li>
      <li><strong>Estrogen &amp; Progesterone</strong>: Vital for reproductive health, but also affect mood swings, anxiety, and depression.</li>
      <li><strong>Insulin</strong>: Balances blood sugar and, indirectly, emotional energy levels.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Disruptions in any of these hormones can lead to mood instability, fatigue, or chronic stress.
      Diet is one of the most powerful tools we have to help restore that balance.
    </p>
  </article>

  <!--—‑‑  Section 3  —‑‑-->
  <article class="section">
    <h2>🥦 How Plant‑Based Diets Support Hormonal Harmony</h2>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Rich in Fiber for Estrogen Regulation:</strong> High‑fiber foods like lentils, oats, flaxseeds, and leafy greens help the body excrete excess estrogen.</li>
      <li><strong>Phytoestrogens for Gentle Hormonal Support:</strong> Compounds in soy, flax, and chickpeas can modulate estrogen levels—especially helpful during menopause or perimenopause.</li>
      <li><strong>Stable Blood Sugar for Emotional Balance:</strong> Whole plant foods regulate insulin and avoid sugar spikes, preventing irritability and cortisol surges.</li>
      <li><strong>Omega‑3s from Plant Sources:</strong> Chia seeds, walnuts, and algae provide omega‑3s that support neurotransmitter function and reduce inflammation.</li>
    </ol>
  </article>

  <!--—‑‑  Section 4  —‑‑-->
  <article class="section">
    <h2>🍲 Sample Plant‑Based Ingredients That Support Hormonal Health</h2>

    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Ingredient</th>
          <th>Key Nutrients</th>
          <th>Hormonal Benefit</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Spinach</td>
          <td>Magnesium, folate</td>
          <td>Calms the nervous system</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Flaxseeds</td>
          <td>Lignans, omega‑3s</td>
          <td>Modulates estrogen</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Avocado</td>
          <td>Healthy fats, B vitamins</td>
          <td>Supports adrenal health</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Chickpeas</td>
          <td>Protein, phytoestrogens</td>
          <td>Stabilizes blood sugar</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Sweet Potato</td>
          <td>Beta‑carotene, fiber</td>
          <td>Aids progesterone production</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </article>

  <!--—‑‑  Section 5  —‑‑-->
  <article class="section">
    <h2>🧘 Emotional &amp; Spiritual Impact of Balanced Hormones</h2>
    <p>
      From a holistic or spiritual perspective, hormonal harmony allows for emotional clarity, mental presence,
      and even deepened self‑awareness. Plant‑based eating is often associated with increased mindfulness and compassion—
      both of which are amplified when physical discomfort or mood instability are reduced.
    </p>
  </article>

  <!--—‑‑  Section 6  —‑‑-->
  <article class="section">
    <h2>✅ Practical Tips to Optimize Hormonal Balance with Food</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Eat colorful vegetables at every meal</li>
      <li>Include healthy fats (e.g., avocado, olive oil, nuts)</li>
      <li>Avoid refined sugars and processed snacks</li>
      <li>Choose whole grains like quinoa or brown rice</li>
      <li>Drink herbal teas such as chamomile or tulsi to support cortisol regulation</li>
    </ul>
  </article>

  <!--—‑‑  結語  —‑‑-->
  <footer class="conclusion">
    <p>
      A plant‑based diet can do more than nourish the body—it can help realign the mind and balance the emotions by
      supporting key hormones. With mindful eating and the right ingredients, meals can become a powerful tool for
      emotional resilience and inner harmony.
    </p>
  </footer>

